'''Lo and behold''' is an expression which can be generally interpreted as a synonym to ''suddenly''. The ''lo'' from the expression likely originated from the shortening of the word ''loke'', commonly seen in [[Middle English]] texts. Its presence in literature can be traced as far back as the [[1800s]].

Through analysis, it is possible to reach the conclusion that said expression is a redundancy, as it literally mean "look and look".

